fields.name: Tetanus
fields.notes:
* aka lockjaw
* bacterial infection
* characterized by muscle spasms
* ~11% of cases proves to be fatal [[source](https://www.cdc.gov/vaccines/pubs/pinkbook/tetanus.html)]
* occurs in all parts of the world but is most frequent in hot and wet climates where the soil has a high organic content [[source](https://www.cdc.gov/vaccines/pubs/pinkbook/tetanus.html)]
* Harvard Medical School: [Do adults really need tetanus booster shots?](https://www.health.harvard.edu/blog/do-adults-really-need-tetanus-booster-shots-2020051219786)
